This paper is about natural language processing and neural networks, which are both core topics in the computer science sub-category of "Computation and Language" (cs.CL). The paper also mentions the use of graph neural networks, which are a popular topic in the sub-category of "Machine Learning" (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves reasoning and understanding of input data, which are key concepts in the sub-categories of "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI) and "Neural and Evolutionary Computing" (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates the models on summarization tasks, which are commonly studied in the sub-category of "Information Retrieval" (cs.IR).
